        Description copied from interface: TerminologyService
        Creates a translator for given set of codings according to the specified concept map. See also: https://www.hl7.org/fhir/operation-conceptmap-translate.html.

        Should be able to ignore codings including are undefined (i.e. the system or code is null).

        Specified by:
        translate in interface TerminologyService
        Parameters:
        codings - the collections of codings to find translations for.
        conceptMapUrl - the url of the concept map to use for translation.
        reverse - reverse true if true.
        equivalences - the equivalences to consider for translation.
        Returns:
        the translator instance with requested translation.

      • getSubsumesRelation

        @Nonnull
public Relation getSubsumesRelation​(@Nonnull
                                    Collection<SimpleCoding> systemAndCodes)
        Description copied from interface: TerminologyService
        Creates a transitive closure representation of subsumes relation for the given set of codings.

        Should be able to ignore codings including are undefined (i.e. the system or code is null) or where the system is unknown to the underlying terminology service.

        Additional resources on closure table maintenance: Maintaining a Closure Table

        Specified by:
        getSubsumesRelation in interface TerminologyService
        Parameters:
        systemAndCodes - the codings to construct the closure for.
        Returns:
        the closure representation.

        Intersects the given set of codings with the ValueSet defined by provided uri.

        Should be able to ignore codings including are undefined (i.e. the system or code is null) or where the system is unknown to the underlying terminology service.

        Specified by:
